   Ci-dessous vous trouverez plus d’informations concernant l’api Worldease.  &nbsp;  L'API WE est disponible uniquement en Restful.  &nbsp;  &nbsp;  In short:  Steps for UPS Integration:  1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sign Up on&nbsp;ups.com.  2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Access Developer Portal  Navigate to the UPS Developer Portal.  Create an application to obtain your Client ID and Client Secret.  3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Implement Authentication  Use OAuth 2.0 for API authorization.  If you are handling the implementation yourself, apply the OAuth Client Credentials flow.  4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Integrate APIs:  Implement the following:  UPS Shipping API  UPS World Ease (WE) API  &nbsp;  Steps to Create a World Ease (WE) Movement  1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Create the Worldease Master Shipment  This serves as the main shipment container.  2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Create the Child Shipments  Link each child shipment to the WE master shipment by including the GCCN number in the shipment payload.  3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Close the Worldease Master Movement  Complete and close the master movement within 7 days.  In detail:  How to get started.   Please sign up on&nbsp;https://www.ups.com/fr/en/home&nbsp;&nbsp;and follow the steps described in the attached document “New User and API key1.PDF. ( Le client doit effectuer cette étape).   UPS API :   OAuth2.0 Security model&nbsp;:   You will have to implement OAuth2.0 security model to connect to the UPS API.  With the “client ID” and “client secret” obtained in the previous steps (New User and API key1.PDF), you can request a bearer token.  The token will be valid for 4 hours. Note: As of 1/4/2026, the token will be valid for only 1 hour.  If you are doing the IT integration yourself, please implement OAuth Client Credentials.  Detailed information is available in the UPS Developer Portal: &nbsp; &nbsp;https://developer.ups.com/catalog?loc=en_FR  Endpoints:  ·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Test :&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;https://wwwcie.ups.com/security/v1/oauth/token  ·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Production :&nbsp;&nbsp;https://onlinetools.ups.com/security/v1/oauth/token  &nbsp;    &nbsp;  &nbsp;    &nbsp;   UPS Shipping API and Worldease API :   &nbsp;  UPS Shipping API catalogue: &nbsp;&nbsp;https://developer.ups.com/tag/Shipping?loc=en_FR  Endpoints:  ·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Test :&nbsp;&nbsp;https://wwwcie.ups.com/api/shipments/v2409/ship  ·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Production :&nbsp;&nbsp;https://onlinetools.ups.com/api/shipments/v2409/ship  &nbsp;  &nbsp;  Find below more information how create a Worldease movement via Worldease API.  &nbsp;  1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Create a master shipment /virtual docbox shipment. ( See samples Worldease Shipping API.zip)  a.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Create a master shipment/ docbox shipment by adding the "MasterHasDocBox": "0" tag in the shipment request.  Add dummy product data in the "InternationalForms" container.  b.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the shipment response, you will get the ShipmentIdentificationNumber and GCCN.&nbsp; Save these details.  &nbsp;  2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Create the child shipments. ( See samples Worldease Shipping API.zip)  a.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Create the child shipment. Add the GCCN in the shipment request.  Important note:  ·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You have up to 7 days to create the child shipments and to close the Worldease movement.  ·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If you want to delete a child shipment from the Worldease movement, you can send a delete request.  Detailed information can be found: &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;https://developer.ups.com/tag/World-Ease-Shipment-Management-Shipment?loc=en_FR&amp;tag=World-Ease-Shipment-Management-Shipment#operation/deleteChildShipment  &nbsp;  Delete request:  Test Endpoint: &nbsp;https://wwwcie.ups.com/api/ship/{version}/child-shipment/{shipment-gccn}/{tracking-number}  Production Endpoint: &nbsp;https://onlinetools.ups.com/api/ship/{version}/child-shipment/{shipment-gccn}/{tracking-number}  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fill in shipment GCCN and tracking nr.  &nbsp;    3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Close the Worldease movement. &nbsp;  a.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Send a “close out shipment request”.  b.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;See below sample request:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;https://developer.ups.com/tag/World-Ease-Shipment-Management-Shipment?loc=en_FR&amp;tag=World-Ease-Shipment-Management-Shipment#operation/saveCloseOutShipment  &nbsp;  Post request:  Test Endpoint:&nbsp;&nbsp;https://wwwcie.ups.com/api/ship/{version}/master-shipment/closeout/{shipment-gccn}&nbsp;&nbsp;  Production Endpoint:&nbsp;&nbsp;https://onlinetools.ups.com/api/ship/{version}/master-shipment/closeout/{shipment-gccn}  Fill in shipment GCCN  &nbsp;  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  &nbsp;  API documentation :&nbsp;API Catalogue | UPS  &nbsp;  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; POE table will have to be shared to customer.

